cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper focuses on unsupervised representation learning for domain generalization, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed method involves learning semantic and shape biased representations, which are also relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the use of jigsaw puzzles for autonomous exploration suggests a potential connection to neural networks (cs.NE).
